## Skill: Priority Scoring

**Purpose**: Apply consistent, objective scoring for roadmap sequencing and strategic comparisons.

**When to Use**: Comparing strategic options, ranking backlog items for roadmap placement. Note: PRDs use timeline-based prioritization rather than this scoring formula.

### Formula

```
Priority Score = (0.2 × SignalStrength) + (0.4 × StrategicFit) + (0.3 × Impact) - (0.1 × Complexity)
```

Score range: 0.0 to 10.0

### Component Calculations

#### SignalStrength (20%)

```
SignalStrength = (0.4 × CustomerScore) + (0.3 × RecencyScore) + (0.2 × DiversityScore) + (0.1 × FrequencyScore)
```

| CustomerScore | Accounts |
|---------------|----------|
| 3.0 | 1 account |
| 5.0 | 2 accounts |
| 7.0 | 3 accounts |
| 9.0 | 4+ accounts |
| 10.0 | 6+ accounts |

| RecencyScore | Days Ago |
|--------------|----------|
| 10.0 | <7 days |
| 8.0 | 7-14 days |
| 6.0 | 14-30 days |
| 4.0 | 30-60 days |
| 2.0 | 60-90 days |

#### StrategicFit (40%)

| Score | Criteria |
|-------|----------|
| 8-10 | Directly advances top-tier strategic goals |
| 5-7 | Supports goals indirectly, table-stakes feature |
| 1-4 | Tangential, one-off request |

#### Impact (30%)

| Score | Criteria |
|-------|----------|
| 9-10 | 20%+ improvement in primary metric, unlocks new segment |
| 7-8 | 10-20% improvement, addresses top-3 issue |
| 5-6 | 5-10% improvement, incremental |
| 3-4 | <5% improvement, unclear impact |
| 1-2 | No clear metric impact |

#### Complexity (10%, negative weight)

```
Complexity = (0.4 × TechnicalComplexity) + (0.4 × TimeEstimate) + (0.2 × RiskLevel)
```

| Technical | Scope |
|-----------|-------|
| 2-3 | Single system/surface |
| 4-6 | Multiple systems |
| 7-8 | Cross-platform + integrations |
| 9-10 | Major architectural change |

### Priority Tiers

| Score | Tier | Placement |
|-------|------|-----------|
| 8.0-10.0 | High Priority | Near-term roadmap |
| 5.0-7.9 | Medium Priority | Mid-term backlog |
| <5.0 | Low Priority | Long-term or deferred |

